In [9]:
# In this project, I am going to define a flight which is going to late or not. I got a ARR_DELAY data that
# describe this information. It include positive and negative number values. For positive values, it mean that
# this flight was late with a specific minutes. In the other side, negative value describes that the flight was
# ready earlier than schedule time or 0 values describes that the flight was ready on time.
In [10]:
# In this data I have three features that describe for departure information of the flight:
# ARR_DELAY: Arrival delay time
 # CRS_ARR_TIME: Scheduled arrival time
# ARR_TIME: Actual departure time
# So I got ARR_DELAY = ARR_TIME - CRS_ARR_TIME. Base on this information, I decided to delete ARR_TIME, 
# CRS_ARR_TIME columns. ARR_DELAY feature already included the information of ARR_TIME and CRS_ARR_TIME feature.
In [11]:
# With the condition: "A flight only counts as late if it is more than 30 minutes late". So I am going to create 
# a target value that include 0(not late) and 1(late) values depending on the condition.
In [12]:
data["TARGET"] = data.ARR_DELAY.apply(lambda x: 1 if x>30 else 0)
In [13]:
# Delete ARR_TIME and CRS_ARR_TIME feature
data = data.drop(['ARR_TIME','CRS_ARR_TIME','ARR_DELAY'],1)

# Scikit-learn provides LabelEncoder library for encoding labels with a value between 0 and one less than 
# the number of discrete classes. I am going to use it to convert my category feature features.
In [16]:
from sklearn import preprocessing
#creating labelEncoder
le = preprocessing.LabelEncoder()

#For OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER feature
OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER_NUM = le.fit_transform(data.OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER)
print("OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER_NUM: ",OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER_NUM)
data["OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER_NUM"] = OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER_NUM

# For ORIGIN feature
ORIGIN_NUM = le.fit_transform(data.ORIGIN)
print("ORIGIN_NUM: ",ORIGIN_NUM)
data["ORIGIN_NUM"] = ORIGIN_NUM

# For DEST feature
DEST_NUM = le.fit_transform(data.DEST)
print("DEST_NUM: ",DEST_NUM)
data["DEST_NUM"] = DEST_NUM
